<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
  ============================================================
  GLASSES BLINK
  A Sound of Someone project by Ziya
  Single-file website: HTML + CSS + JavaScript + documentation
  ============================================================

  CONCEPT
  Glasses Blink turns the sound of glassware — the kind we hear
  every day, almost without noticing — into music. Four families
  of glass (wine, tumbler, flute, crystal), each with its own
  inharmonic timbre, can be tapped, held, swept, and re-poured
  in real time. Eight glasses are tuned to a C major pentatonic
  scale, so any combination of notes sounds harmonious.

  HOW TO PLAY
    - Click any glass to tap it (short ring).
    - Hold to sustain the tone (like a wet finger on a rim).
    - Drag across the row while holding to play a glissando.
    - Keys A S D F G H J K map to the eight glasses.
    - Switch glass family with the Wine / Tumbler / Flute /
      Crystal tabs at the top.
    - Toggle Tune mode to drag a glass up or down to retune it.
    - Record / Play Loop / Clear capture and replay phrases.

  TECHNICAL NOTES
    - Sound: Web Audio API. Per-note inharmonic synthesis using
      4–5 sine partials at glass-specific ratios; tap envelope
      uses exponential decay (1.8s tumbler → 6.5s crystal);
      sustain envelope adds vibrato (~5 Hz, ~5 cents) and a
      0.6s release. A 2.4s algorithmic reverb adds room ambience.
    - Tuning: pitch = 220 · 2^((100 - waterLevel) / 50).
    - Visuals: pure HTML/CSS, no images. Each glass family has
      its own silhouette and glow color.
    - Recording stores the glass family on each event so loops
      replay across the correct families.

  Click the small "?" in the top-right while running for the
  in-page about panel.
-->
